reviews.text: Visit there long time ago with excellent food.  Now excitement.  Might be downgraded.

Terrible service, I ordered a meal and they put a different meal on the table. After asking a member of staff and realising what I was eating wasn't part of my meal, their only reply was "too bad, you already ate it". Neither the quality of food nor the pricing was any better than other Japanese restaurants nearby.  Other 5 stars reviews likely made by their own members of staff.

I gave this restaurant five star not only because of their wonderful food (the seared halibut and mentaiko fried rice was amazingggggg), but the staff were very dedicated and caring! Impressive hospitality! I'm super impressed and satisfied with the food and service.  MUST TRY!!!!!!!!!!!!

reviews.text: Reasonably priced Japanese restaurant. It's a Japanese izakaya that serves a wide range of Japanese food. Went there on Saturday night and it was quite full. So make sure you reserve a table first. There were five of us the dinner came out to be around $260pp. I would recommend their beef tongue skewer, bacon lychee skewer (weird ad it may sound), ramen salad and their sashimi which was quite fresh.
Try the soft shell crab sushi....amazing 🍣
家庭式居酒屋，水準一貫有保證！
好好味😋
